subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis:
A member of the genus 

Sphaenorhynchus

in the sense of 

Faivovich 
et al.
(
2005
)

, characterized by the following combination of characters: (
1
) size small for the genus, SVL 
15.7–18.2 mm
in males; (
2
) snout truncate in dorsal view, rounded, slightly acute in profile; (
3
) tympanum concealed; (
4
) vocal sac developed, single, subgular, extending to the chest and entering the arms, whithout longitudinal lateral folds; (
5
) vomerine teeth absent; (
6
) absence of a black line from the tip of snout to eye; (
7
) absence of distinctive longitudinal white spot under the eye; (
8
) absence of white stripe or brown lines on dorsolateral region.

Color: In life, dorsum and limbs uniformly bright green (
Fig. 6
), with white dots scattered without forming defined pattern; vocal sac and belly whitish green; fingers and toes yellowish green. Iris silvery golden, with few black vermiculations.
